    <goal>Create docs/architecture/scope-architecture.md — document scope inheritance, resolution chain, and fallback behavior</goal>
    <context>The Spaarke platform uses a scope system to control AI behavior, configuration, and feature availability. Scopes form an inheritance hierarchy with resolution chains and fallback behavior. No architecture document captures this scope system end-to-end.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use /docs-architecture skill structure
      - Source ALL content from actual code — do not invent scope behaviors
      - Document scope hierarchy: global → organization → matter → document levels
      - Map the resolution chain: how scope values are resolved with inheritance and override
      - Document fallback behavior when a scope value is not defined at a level
      - Include scope storage and retrieval from Dataverse
      - Cite source files for every component
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
